      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "6126dbb9ef8fc39d",
      "text": "This year has brought a number of budget cuts in our district. Looking ahead, the future doesn't look bright fiscally. PERS costs are going to explode out of control over the next 5-10 years. Next year alone, we're looking at PERS increases of over $2 million compared to an operating budget of around $50 million. That's a huge chunk of money for us to find. We're trying and needing to get by with less. "
    },
